The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Murali, Arnold recalled

Colombo: Sri Lanka recalled Muttiah Muralidharan on Wednesday in naming a 14-man squad for the two-Test series against West Indies. 

The 33-year-old off-spinner, returns for the first time since August last year after recovering from two shoulder operations. 

Muralidharan, who has taken 532 wickets in 91 Tests, missed series against South Africa, Pakistan and New Zealand during his absence, the longest layoff of his career. 

Middle-order batsman Russel Arnold was also recalled after a year-long absence having impressed with Sri Lanka A. 

Fast bowler Nuwan Zoysa returns after successful knee surgery and uncapped allrounder Gayan Wijekoon has been picked for the first time. 

THE SQUAD 

Maravan Atapattu, Mahela Jayawardene, Kumar Sangakkara, Sanath Jayasuriya, Chaminda Vaas, Muttiah Muralidharan, Thilan Samaraweera, Tillakaratne Dilshan, Russel Arnold, Lasith Malinga, Nuwan Zoysa, Upul Chandana, Rangana Herath, Gayan Wijekoon. 

